## Requirements

### R1: TypedAgent Trait

Define `TypedAgent<I, O>` generic trait:

```rust
#[async_trait]
pub trait TypedAgent<I, O>
where
    I: Serialize + DeserializeOwned + Send + Sync,
    O: Serialize + DeserializeOwned + Send + Sync,
{
    async fn run(&self, input: I) -> NovaResult<O>;
    fn name(&self) -> &str;
}
```

### R2: Standard Input Schema

```json
{
  "type": "object",
  "properties": {
    "intent": { "type": "string", "description": "User's raw description/request" },
    "project_id": { "type": "string", "description": "Project identifier for SpecStore lookup" },
    "clarifications": {
      "type": "array",
      "items": {
        "type": "object",
        "properties": {
          "question": { "type": "string" },
          "answer": { "type": "string" }
        },
        "required": ["question", "answer"]
      }
    }
  },
  "required": ["intent", "project_id"]
}
```

### R3: Standard Output Schema (Discriminated Union)

```json
{
  "oneOf": [
    {
      "type": "object",
      "properties": {
        "type": { "const": "need_clarification" },
        "questions": {
          "type": "array",
          "items": {
            "type": "object",
            "properties": {
              "id": { "type": "string" },
              "question": { "type": "string" },
              "why": { "type": "string" },
              "suggestions": { "type": "array", "items": { "type": "string" } }
            },
            "required": ["id", "question", "why"]
          }
        }
      },
      "required": ["type", "questions"]
    },
    {
      "type": "object",
      "properties": {
        "type": { "const": "create_issues" },
        "issues": {
          "type": "array",
          "items": {
            "type": "object",
            "properties": {
              "title": { "type": "string" },
              "description": { "type": "string" },
              "issue_type": { "enum": ["feature", "bug", "refactor", "chore"] },
              "priority": { "enum": ["P0", "P1", "P2", "P3"] },
              "labels": { "type": "array", "items": { "type": "string" } },
              "acceptance_criteria": { "type": "array", "items": { "type": "string" } },
              "depends_on": { "type": "array", "items": { "type": "string" } },
              "scope": { "enum": ["small", "medium", "large"] }
            },
            "required": ["title", "description", "issue_type", "priority", "acceptance_criteria"]
          }
        },
        "summary": { "type": "string" }
      },
      "required": ["type", "issues", "summary"]
    }
  ]
}
```

### R4: SpecStore Dependency

```rust
#[async_trait]
pub trait SpecStore: Send + Sync {
    async fn search(&self, query: &str, project_id: &str) -> NovaResult<Vec<SpecRef>>;
    async fn read(&self, spec_id: &str, project_id: &str) -> NovaResult<String>;
}

pub struct SpecRef {
    pub spec_id: String,
    pub title: String,
    pub relevance: f32,
}
```

### R5: Agent Implementation

```rust
pub struct RestructureAgent {
    provider: Arc<dyn LLMProvider>,
    spec_store: Arc<dyn SpecStore>,
    model: String,
}
```

- System prompt loaded via `include_str!("../../prompts/restructure.md")`
- Calls `complete_structured()` with R3 JSON Schema
- Module: `crates/cclab-agent/src/agents/restructure/` (mod.rs + types.rs)
- Builder: `RestructureAgentBuilder`
